div.p:
Futhermore, all who know your Ladiship, and know the perpetuall attendance of my Lord, your vvorthy and right honourable husband, on his Maiesty at Court, will beare you record, that you indeed are the vertuous Woman, of whom Salomon saith, that THE HEART OF HER HVSBAND DOTH SAFELY TRVST IN HER;

that her children arise and call her blessed; that her husband praiseth her, and saith, MANY DAVGHTERS HAVE DONE VERTVOVSLY, BVT THOV EXCELLEST THEM ALL. You are the last and most sure receiver of my Lords debts: you are the most faithfull keeper of his treasures and Registers: Let it please you then, most vertuous and Noble LADY, receive this obligatorie bill, whereby I acknowledge my selfe indebted to my Lord for his favour and kindnesse, and doe bind me by it, as by a solemne contract, to powre out my soule before the Lord of Lords, day and night; beseeching his divine Maiestie to

powre downe upon your right honourable persons and hopefull issue, all kind of blessings externall, internall, and eternall, for Christ Iesus his Sons sake; in whom I am, and shall remaine for ever,
